wikipedia_page.main: Maurice "Matt" Woods (1 November 1931 – 26 September 2014) was a professional footballer who played for Everton, Blackburn Rovers, Sydney Hakoah, Luton Town and Stockport County.

* Matt Woods, a footballer, was born in Skelmersdale. He played for multiple clubs, but most notably Everton F.C. and Blackburn Rovers F.C.
